<subSubSection id="00D41B90257B9B50FEEC98D2C74FFE0C" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4871481B257B9B50FEEC98D2C74FFE0C" blockId="8.[264,1324,1761,1868]" lastBlockId="9.[264,1324,284,670]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="7ABA9409257B9B51FEEC98D2C3DAF921" bold="true" box="[264,392,1761,1787]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Prostomium prolobic to proepilobic. Setae lumbricine. Male pores paired, in seminal grooves, on 
<number id="FE065A3C257B9B51FE1A9939C04CF8FE" box="[510,542,1802,1828]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="18.0">18</number>
; prostatic pores paired, at ends of seminal grooves, on 
<number id="FE065A3C257B9B51FB4B9939C69EF8FE" box="[1199,1228,1802,1828]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="17.0">17</number>
and 
<number id="FE065A3C257B9B51FAEC9939C77BF8FE" box="[1288,1321,1802,1828]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="19.0">19</number>
. Oesophagus with a single gizzard in 
<number id="FE065A3C257B9B51FD3A9901C0BDF896" box="[734,751,1842,1868]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="5.0">5</number>
; much enlarged in 
<number id="FE065A3C257B9B51FC0C9901C657F896" box="[1000,1029,1842,1868]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="16.0">16</number>
with calciferous ridges extending to 
<number id="FE065A3C257A9B50FE4C9F2FC39AFEEC" box="[424,456,284,310]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="18.0">18</number>
; discrete calciferous glands, intestinal caeca and supra­intestinal glands absent; typhlosole lamelliform, simple. Penial setae present. Micromeronephridia astomate, exonephric, small paired tufts on body wall in 
<number id="FE065A3C257A9B50FC649F5FC1FCFE5C" box="[896,942,364,390]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
, on septa in 
<number id="FE065A3C257A9B50FBA39F5FC6D6FE5C" box="[1095,1156,364,390]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="8.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="5.0">5–12</number>
, in clusters of 
<quantity id="8F36E5FE257A9B50FEEC9FA7C301FE74" box="[264,339,404,430]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.143" metricValueMax="1.27" metricValueMin="1.016" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="in" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 in</quantity>
<number id="FE065A3C257A9B50FEBE9FA7C325FE74" box="[346,375,404,430]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="13.0">13</number>
and posteriad segments; paired, stomate, exonephric megameronephridia lateral to micromeronephridia in 
<number id="FE065A3C257A9B50FDDF9F8FC00AFE0C" box="[571,600,444,470]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="17.0">17</number>
and posteriad segments, funnels at or lateral to 
<emphasis id="7ABA9409257A9B50FB6C9F8FC6C5FE0F" box="[1160,1175,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">b</emphasis>
lines in 
<emphasis id="7ABA9409257A9B50FB1F9F8FC745FE0F" box="[1275,1303,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">bc</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="00D41B90257A9B50FEDC9FD7C0C8FD44" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="4871481B257A9B50FEDC9FD7C0C8FD44" blockId="9.[264,1324,284,670]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName id="8FCE3398257A9B50FEDC9FD7C394FE27" box="[312,454,484,509]" class="Clitellata" family="Octochaetidae" genus="Shimodrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="7ABA9409257A9B50FEDC9FD7C394FE27" box="[312,454,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Shimodrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="61892972257A9B50FE299FD7C06BFE24" box="[461,569,484,510]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to a group of Oriental octochaetid genera with a single oesophageal gizzard and stomate exonephric megameronephridia but without discrete calciferous glands. It can be distinguished form other members of the group, 
<taxonomicName id="8FCE3398257A9B50FB259C07C38FFDAC" authority="Stephenson, 1921" authorityName="Stephenson" authorityYear="1921" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Ramiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crassiclitellata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7ABA9409257A9B50FB259C07C779FD97" box="[1217,1323,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Ramiella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2C5F35EA257A9B50FEEC9C6FC38FFDAC" author="Stephenson" box="[264,477,604,630]" pageId="9" pageNumber="27" refString="Stephenson, J. (1921) Contributions to the morphology, classification, and zoogeography of India Oligochaeta. I. The affinities and systematic position of the genus Eudichogaster Michaelsen, and some related questions. II. On polyphyly in the Oligochaeta. III. Some general considerations in the geographical distribution of Indian Oligochaeta. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1921, 103 - 142." type="proceedings paper" year="1921">
Stephenson, 
<number id="FE065A3C257A9B50FE449C6FC38FFDAC" box="[416,477,604,630]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1921.0">1921</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="7ABA9409257A9B50FE099C6FC03CFDAF" box="[493,622,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mallehulla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2C5F35EA257A9B50FD9C9C6FC123FDAC" author="Julka" box="[632,881,604,630]" pageId="9" pageNumber="26" refString="Julka, J. M. &amp; Rao, B. R. (1982) A new earthworm Mallehulla indica gen. et sp. nov. (Oligochaeta: Octochaetidae) from Karnataka, India. Journal of Soil Biology and Ecology, 2 (2), 67 - 72." type="journal article" year="1982">
Julka and Rao, 
<number id="FE065A3C257A9B50FCD29C6FC123FDAC" box="[822,881,604,630]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1982.0">1982</number>
